      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKIBEQUICK (10) did a good job to come from a wide barrier and finish fourth last start in stronger company at Goulburn. Draws on the back row but this is the lowest graded race he has contested for some time. HUNTER SHANNON (6) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when third in tougher grade at this venue. Draws wider but finds a nice race so with even luck he could rediscover winning form. BETTOR KEPPEL (3) draws well and comes right into contention after coming from the back row and scoring last start by 1.2 metres at this circuit and distance. GO WITHOUT (7) draws wider but comes off a respectable third to a smart one at his most recent appearance and he was a winner over this shorter distance here three back.",
